msgid "How inclusive is my conference?"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:6
msgid ""
"A checklist for conference organisers based on the [DISCOVER "
"cookbook](https://discover-cookbook.numfocus.org/intro.html)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:8
msgid "Organizing committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:9
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:23
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:32
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:50
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:61
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:66
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:75
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:79
msgid "‚úÖ High effort, high impact"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:10
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> The organizing committee itself should reflect "
"the diversity you want to create in your conference. Consider age/career "
"stage, gender, race, sexual orientation, social and professional "
"background when assembling your committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:12
msgid "Venue"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:13
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:28
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:36
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:45
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:55
#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:70
msgid "üçé Low effort, high impact"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:14
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Seats reserved for wheelchair users and other "
"mobility-impaired people"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:15
msgid "<input type=\"checkbox\"> Wide aisles between chairs for easy navigation"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:16
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Large text signs and easy-to-read maps for "
"people with impaired vision"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:17
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Bathrooms: signs posted in restrooms that say "
"something along the following lines: \"If you think someone's gender "
"doesn't match the sign on the door, please follow these steps: Don't "
"worry about it, they know better than you.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:18
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Tampons and pads in all restrooms (some people "
"who identify as male have periods and may need them)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:19
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Nursing and pumping room: Clearly labelled, "
"single-occupancy room with lock dedicated as nursing and pumping room"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:20
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Bottle-feeding room: Clearly labelled, gender-"
"neutral, multiple-occupancy room for bottle-feeding babies (different "
"from nursing and pumping room!)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:21
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Quiet room: dedicated room for people to take a"
" break (no phones, no talking, no notification beeps!) which can also be "
"used as a prayer room"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:24
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Sign-language interpreters or real-time "
"captioning in place for people with hearing impairment"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:25
msgid "<input type=\"checkbox\"> Easily accessible gender-neutral bathrooms"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:27
msgid "Catering"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:29
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Labels in front of each dish with list of "
"ingredients and common labels/allergens (e.g. \"gluten free\", "
"\"kosher\", \"includes peanuts\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:30
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> A variety of beverages, in particular non-"
"alcoholic and non-caffeinated"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:33
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Planned for the following dietary needs: gluten"
" free, dairy free, vegan, vegetarian, pork free, shellfish free, soy "
"free, nut free - especially peanut (this is usually a serious allergy so "
"take extra care), kosher, halal"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:35
msgid "Code of Conduct"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:37
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Code of Conduct (CoC) in place ([example "
"here](https://confcodeofconduct.com))"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:38
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Tick box at registration where every "
"participant confirms that they have read the CoC"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:39
msgid "<input type=\"checkbox\"> Copy of CoC included in sponsor packet"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:40
msgid "<input type=\"checkbox\"> CoC easily accessible on conference website"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:41
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Short version included in the printed schedule "
"as reminder"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:42
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Mentions in welcome talks and at start of every"
" day, including who to contact if there is a problem"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:44
msgid "Participant and Speaker Selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:46
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Considered specific wording of how talks were "
"solicited so as not to put people with diverse backgrounds off (e.g. call"
" for \"speakers who have advice or expertise to share\" rather than "
"\"experts in best practices)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:47
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Call for Proposals: Are you transparent that "
"you want a broad and diverse group to share expertise? What are the "
"criteria that will be used to assess their submissions? How and why are "
"you trying to shake things up regarding diversity and inclusion compared "
"to previous conferences?"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:48
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Attracting attendees: Considered what kind of "
"photos you use to advertise your event and what kind of message that "
"sends about diversity and inclusion"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:51
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Invited Speakers: Reached beyond the conference"
" organizers' own network and the circle of usual suspects to solicit "
"speakers"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:52
#, python-format
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Review of submitted proposals: There is no 100%"
" guaranteed way to avoid bias, but have you done everything you can to "
"mitigate bias in the review process (e.g. by choosing double-blind "
"review)?"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:54
msgid "Event Registration"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:56
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Can registrants request additional "
"accessibility support?"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:57
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Can registrants specify dietary restrictions, "
"in particular severe allergies?"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:58
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Can registrants opt out of having their photos "
"taken at the event?"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:59
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Is there a check-box for registrants to "
"indicate that they have read the Code of Conduct?"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:62
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Demographic information is better collected "
"during a post-conference survey, but if you do collect demographic info: "
"are you thoughtful in what you ask and how so as not to alienate people?"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:63
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Sufficient measures for anonymity and data "
"security in place"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:65
msgid "Childcare"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:67
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Offering financial support for childcare, "
"either through childcare grant or onsite services"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:69
msgid "Check-in"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:71
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> System for photography opt-outs in place (e.g. "
"by adding sticker or lanyard to conference badge)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:72
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Pronoun pins (he/him, she/her, they/them), "
"buttons or ribbons in place (optimally colour-coded)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:74
msgid "Grants/Scholarships"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:76
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Offering grants to support attendance of "
"traditionally underrepresented and/or marginalized groups in technology "
"and/or open source communities (including persons identifying as LGBTQ, "
"indigenous, women, persons of color, and/or persons with disabilities) "
"who otherwise wouldn't have the means to participate"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:78
msgid "Assessment of event"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/13_inclusive-checklist.md:80
msgid ""
"<input type=\"checkbox\"> Post-event survey of participants to establish "
"whether your diversity and inclusion measures had an effect"
msgstr ""

